                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>Late 19th or the first half of the 20th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors (often only the
                           second component); incipit of Texts I and II; title of Text I-2; incipit
                           of the sections of the daily readings (homilies, absolution prayers,
                           miracles and ʾarke); selected words or parts of words in ʾarke; words
                           “salām” and “sǝbḥat” in Text II; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 
 A few groups of lines on the
                           incipit page of Text I; a few groups of lines of the incipit of Texts I-2
                           to I-8.
 The first and the last letters or every second letter are
                           rubricated in the nomina sacra on fols. 29vb, 50rb, 61ra, 69rab,
                           83rb.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Text II is written in smaller
                        script.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week written in upper margin, encircled with alternating
                              red and black dots, in the main hand: ዘሰሉስ: <locus target="#18ra">fol.
                                 18ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#31vb">fol. 31vb</locus> ዘሐሙስ:
                                 <locus target="#42rb">fol. 42rb</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#55rb">fol. 55rb</locus> ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#67va">fol. 67va</locus>
                              ዘዕሑድ: <locus target="#79va">fol. 79va</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Omitted letters and words are written interlineally in the main hand, often in red ink: fols. 5ra, 14vb, 15ra, 16rb, 24ra, 31rb, 36ra, 36va, 40ra, 41va, 43ra, 45va, 49ra, 51ra, 51vb, 53ra, 54vab, 55ra, 55vb, 59ra, 69rb, 71rab, 78ra, 82va, 86vb, 90rb, 94ra. - Erasures: fols. 23vb, 28ra, 78ra. - A few spaces for rubrication are left unfilled on fols. 41ra-42rb. - Scribbles, doodles: fols. 1rv, 2rv, 3r, 4r, 5r, 6r, 7v, 8r, 18ra, 20r, 29v, 38r, 42r, 50v, 51r, 68r, 100v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
